sizes of the droplets are quantified, with multiple droplets being more
  stable at the highest temperature simulated. The droplet is mainly located close
to the saturates molecules in Cooee bitumen.
Finally, it is shown that the water dynamics is much slower in bitumen than in pure water
because it is governed by the diffusion of the droplet and not of the single molecules.

